<div id="residencial-home-tweet-corpus" class="section level1">
<h1>Residencial Home Tweet Corpus</h1>
<p>The <em>corpus</em> consists of 3042 documents (tweets) from 3 actors. The tweets were collected between 2013-11-14 and 2021-05-24. The actors considered were the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>ceap_ps</li>
<li>FEDdependencia</li>
<li>AESTE_oficial</li>
</ul>
<p>The co-variates in the corpus are status_id, screen_name, text, date, after_covid, covid_months. Only tweets issued 12 months before and after the start of the state of emergency (2020-03-14) were considered.</p>
<pre><code>## # A tibble: 10 x 3
##    screen_name   text                                                 date      
##    &lt;chr&gt;         &lt;chr&gt;                                                &lt;date&gt;    
##  1 AESTE_oficial &quot;no te pierdas en  minutos a @jcuberoherr  secretar~ 2020-03-27
##  2 cea_ps        &quot;porque en la atencion profesional no hay distancia~ 2020-11-05
##  3 AESTE_oficial &quot;fundacion memora y el hospital universitario de la~ 2019-08-02
##  4 AESTE_oficial &quot;creemos necesario optimizar los sistemas de barema~ 2019-05-30
##  5 cea_ps        &quot;quieres colaborar en nuestro cuestionario de vacun~ 2021-02-08
##  6 AESTE_oficial &quot;debemos plantearnos la creacion de centros donde s~ 2020-11-06
##  7 cea_ps        &quot;el #miercoles cita en #pamplona con la gestion de ~ 2019-10-06
##  8 AESTE_oficial &quot;afortunadamente parece ser que ya contamos con el ~ 2020-04-01
##  9 AESTE_oficial &quot;hemos solicitado la realizacion de un analisis de ~ 2020-09-22
## 10 AESTE_oficial &quot;el grupo eulen ha contratado a mas de  mujeres vic~ 2019-11-25</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
</div>
<div id="topic-models" class="section level1">
<h1>Topic Models</h1>
<p>Several parameters of <em>k</em> were considered, as well as various models of tokenization and trimming. The latter include uni-grams, bi-grams and corpus/document level term trimming. We settle on Model 3, bi-grams and <span class="math inline">\(k=4\)</span>.</p>
<div id="selecting-k" class="section level3">
<h3>Selecting K</h3>
<pre class="r"><code>dfmat1 &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;% 
  mutate(date=ymd(date),
         after_covid=ifelse(after_covid==1,&quot;After Covid&quot;, &quot;Before Covid&quot;)) %&gt;% 
  filter(date %within% interval(ymd(190314),ymd(210314))) %&gt;% 
  mutate(text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;@[:alnum:]+&quot;),
         text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;#[:alnum:]+&quot;)) %&gt;%
  unnest_tokens(word,text) %&gt;%
  anti_join(esp_stopwords) %&gt;% 
  filter(nchar(word)&gt;=2) %&gt;% 
  count(status_id, word, sort = TRUE) %&gt;% 
  rename(document=status_id,
         term=word,
         count=n) %&gt;% 
  cast_dfm(document, term, count) %&gt;% 
  dfm_trim(max_docfreq = 0.05, min_termfreq = 2, docfreq_type = &quot;prop&quot;)

my_docvars1 &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;% 
  rename(document=status_id,
         actor=screen_name) %&gt;% 
  mutate(document=as.character(document)) %&gt;% 
  select(-text) %&gt;% 
  filter(document %in% rownames(dfmat1))</code></pre>
<p>Spanish <em>stopwords</em> and tokens with a length &lt; 2 were removed, alongside numbers and punctuation.</p>
<ul>
<li>Residuals are minimized at 10</li>
<li>Held-out likelihood is maximized at 2</li>
<li>In both, there is an inflection point at 4 topics.</li>
<li>At <span class="math inline">\(k=4\)</span>, Semantic Coherence and Exclusivity are mostly in the upper right quadrant.</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
</div>
<div id="model-i-unigrams-token-document-frequency" class="section level3">
<h3>Model I (Unigrams / Token-Document Frequency)</h3>
<pre class="r"><code>#Topic Model 1
if(cache==T){
  mystm &lt;- readRDS(&quot;mystm.rds&quot;)
} else {

mystm &lt;- stm(documents = dfmat1, 
             K = 4, 
             data = my_docvars1, 
             init.type = &quot;Spectral&quot;,
             verbose = F
             )
saveRDS(mystm, &quot;mystm.rds&quot;)

}

#Content (beta)
td_beta_stm &lt;- tidy(mystm)

#Prevalence (gamma)
stm_prevalence &lt;- tidy(mystm, matrix = &quot;gamma&quot;,
                     document_names = rownames(dfmat1)
                     ) %&gt;% 
  inner_join(my_docvars1) %&gt;% 
  group_by(date, topic) %&gt;% 
  summarise(topic_av=mean(gamma, na.rm=T))</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
</div>
<div id="model-ii-unigramstoken-frequency" class="section level3">
<h3>Model II (Unigrams/Token Frequency)</h3>
<pre class="r"><code>tokens &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;% 
  mutate(date=ymd(date),
         after_covid=ifelse(after_covid==1,&quot;After Covid&quot;, &quot;Before Covid&quot;)) %&gt;% 
  filter(date %within% interval(ymd(190314),ymd(210314))) %&gt;% 
  mutate(text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;@[:alnum:]+&quot;),
         text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;#[:alnum:]+&quot;)) %&gt;%
  unnest_tokens(word,text) %&gt;%
  anti_join(esp_stopwords) %&gt;% 
  filter(nchar(word)&gt;=2) %&gt;% 
  count(status_id, word, sort = TRUE) %&gt;% 
  rename(document=status_id,
         term=word,
         count=n) </code></pre>
<pre><code>## Joining, by = &quot;word&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>#Text Cleaning
pruned_terms &lt;- tokens %&gt;% 
  group_by(term) %&gt;% 
  summarise(n=n()) %&gt;% 
  mutate(
    prune=ifelse(n&gt;=round(quantile(n, probs = .99), digits = 0),1,0),
    prune=ifelse(n&lt;=round(quantile(n, probs = .01), digits = 0),1,prune),
    ) %&gt;% 
  filter(prune==1) %&gt;% 
  select(term)

dfmat2 &lt;- tokens %&gt;% 
  anti_join(pruned_terms) %&gt;% 
  cast_dfm(document, term, count)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## Joining, by = &quot;term&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>my_docvars2 &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;% 
  rename(document=status_id,
         actor=screen_name) %&gt;% 
  mutate(document=as.character(document)) %&gt;% 
  select(-text) %&gt;% 
  filter(document %in% rownames(dfmat2))</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>#Topic Model 1
if(cache==T){
  mystm2 &lt;- readRDS(&quot;mystm2.rds&quot;)
} else {

mystm2 &lt;- stm(documents = dfmat2, 
             K = 4, 
             prevalence = ~after_covid+actor,
             data = my_docvars2, 
             init.type = &quot;Spectral&quot;,
             verbose = F
             )
saveRDS(mystm2, &quot;mystm2.rds&quot;)

}

#Content (beta)
td_beta_stm2 &lt;- tidy(mystm2)

#Prevalence (gamma)
stm_prevalence2 &lt;- tidy(mystm2, matrix = &quot;gamma&quot;,
                     document_names = rownames(dfmat2)
                     ) %&gt;% 
  inner_join(my_docvars2) %&gt;% 
  group_by(date, topic) %&gt;% 
  summarise(topic_av=mean(gamma, na.rm=T))</code></pre>

<div id="model-iii-bigramstoken-frequency" class="section level3">
<h3>Model III (Bigrams/Token Frequency)</h3>
<pre class="r"><code>#BiGrams
tokens_bigrams &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;%
  mutate(date=ymd(date),
         after_covid=ifelse(after_covid==1,&quot;After Covid&quot;, &quot;Before Covid&quot;)) %&gt;%
  filter(date %within% interval(ymd(190314),ymd(210314))) %&gt;%
  mutate(text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;@[:alnum:]+&quot;),
         text=str_remove_all(text, &quot;#[:alnum:]+&quot;)) %&gt;%
  unnest_tokens(word,text,token = &quot;ngrams&quot;, n = 2) %&gt;%
  separate(word, c(&quot;word1&quot;, &quot;word2&quot;), sep = &quot; &quot;) %&gt;%
  filter(!word1 %in% esp_stopwords$word) %&gt;%
  filter(!word2 %in% esp_stopwords$word) %&gt;%
  filter(nchar(word1)&gt;=2) %&gt;%
  filter(nchar(word2)&gt;=2) %&gt;%
  unite(word, word1, word2, sep = &quot;-&quot;) %&gt;%
  count(status_id, word, sort = TRUE) %&gt;%
  rename(document=status_id,
         term=word,
         count=n) 

pruned_terms_b &lt;- tokens_bigrams %&gt;%
  group_by(term) %&gt;%
  summarise(n=n()) %&gt;%
  mutate(
    prune=ifelse(n&gt;=round(quantile(n, probs = .99), digits = 0),1,0),
    prune=ifelse(n&lt;=round(quantile(n, probs = .01), digits = 0),1,prune),
    ) %&gt;%
  filter(prune==1) %&gt;%
  select(term)

dfmat_bigrams &lt;- tokens_bigrams %&gt;%
  anti_join(pruned_terms_b) %&gt;%
  cast_dfm(document, term, count)

my_docvars_b &lt;- my_corpus %&gt;%
  rename(document=status_id,
         actor=screen_name) %&gt;%
  mutate(document=as.character(document)) %&gt;%
  select(-text) %&gt;%
  filter(document %in% rownames(dfmat_bigrams))

mystm_b &lt;- stm(documents = dfmat_bigrams,
             K = 4,
             prevalence = ~after_covid+actor,
             data = my_docvars_b,
             init.type = &quot;Spectral&quot;,
             verbose = F
             )

#Content (beta)
td_beta_stm_b &lt;- tidy(mystm_b)

#Prevalence (gamma)
stm_prevalence_b &lt;- tidy(mystm_b, matrix = &quot;gamma&quot;,
                     document_names = rownames(dfmat_bigrams)
                     ) %&gt;%
  inner_join(my_docvars_b) %&gt;%
  group_by(date, topic) %&gt;%
  summarise(topic_av=mean(gamma, na.rm=T))</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="672" /></p>
